      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LEAP TO FAME (6) stretched his perfect Inter Dominion record to eight with another dominant performance last week, a remarkable 21st success from 23 attempts at this circuit and distance. Draws one spot wider but expect him to push forward as he did last week. Hard to tip against him once again. THE JANITOR NZ (8) draws the same heat as LEAP TO FAME again after finishing 7m behind him in fourth last week but he was drawn outside the champ on that occasion. Draws the inside of the back row here and the sprint lane is in play. Has a powerful finish so could be dangerous if within striking distance. MAX DELIGHT (11) cops a tougher draw than when third in round one but he was resuming there and strikes at 50 percent when second-up so can progress. TRIEDTOTELLYA (5) was solid enough when fourth last week. Draws wider but he is the sort of horse that can be relied upon to be competitive.",
